node.text:
I had the honor of watching my husband create this TRIBUTE song. As he did his research and organized all the different cases and instances of brutality and murder driven by racism he would point out the different details that happened during and, just as important, AFTER the incident to me. He’d be like, “Babe, remember that case when this that and that happened?, they all got acquitted” “Oh my goodness, Babe look at the video from that time when then said such and such happened but they lied! They got acquitted too.” Words can’t describe how I felt. I went from mad, to sad, to disgusted, to hurt, back to mad again and several other emotions. I had the honor of watching my husband create this TRIBUTE song. As he did his research and organized all the different cases and instances of brutality and murder driven by racism he would point out the different details that happened during and, just as important, AFTER the incident to me. He’d be like, “Babe, remember that case when this that and that happened?, they all got acquitted” “Oh my goodness, Babe look at the video from that time when then said such and such happened but they lied! They got acquitted too.” Words can’t describe how I felt. I went from mad, to sad, to disgusted, to hurt, back to mad again and several other emotions. So many names that didn’t get mentioned in the song; it’s just too many...it’s just too many🙏🏽😔 🎥 @WillC_StreetHeat @Romeo615Videos

Sidebar: Thank fully🙏🏽 I wasn’t walking around in panties & bra with my MeekMillies
Double Sidebar: This “lady” is crazyyyy
Triple Sidebar: Listen to hubby asking about how my day was 🥰 #RemyMa 🎥 @thejasminebrand
